Many people learn better when they learn in groups. Study Jams are community-run study groups for developers covering a range of Google Developers content. Typically, Study Jams focus on completing a course, but some may focus on mastering a skill or product area.

The Study Jams objective is to raise the technical proficiency of global community members through the highest possible course completion rate.

mSite Study Jams

What is mSite Study Jams ?

A professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals who demonstrate understanding in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development.

How long does it take ?

Fairly quick: approximately 3-4 hours of study material, followed by 90 minute (multiple choice) exam.

What is the end result ?

Students that complete the exam receive a printable certificate to verify status as a certified mobile sites professional and a Google Partners public profile page listing the certification

events.name: Flutter Study Jam
events.description:
What?
Flutter Study Jams are Community-run study groups based on the Flutter Udacity Course. Participants learn how to use Flutter to develop high-quality, interactive mobile applications for iOS and Android devices.

Why?
Study Jams are a great opportunity to bring members of your community together to learn Flutter in person and support them to complete the course. Everyone, who completes the course will get a Google-offered Study Jam completion certificate and a profile badge.

Who?
Flutter Study Jam is suited best for: 1) those just getting started with mobile app development 2) those with programming experience on other mobile app frameworks.

Facilitator: Mr. Paras Nath Chaudhary
He is senior developer and CTO at Abhiyantrik Technology. He likes to contribute in community works and volunteer. He has also been active in NOSK, FOSS Nepal, Ubuntu One and GDG.

Time and Date:
24 to 25 November and 1st to 2nd December
Total 12 hours of course structure. 2PM onwards.

Our Partners:
Abhiyantrik Technology, Four Tuples, BoldCode and Google Developers

events.name: Open Data Day 2019, Dang
events.description:
Open Knowledge Nepal is organizing a day-long ‘Data Expedition’ in Dang having GDG Dang as a Community Partner, where around 40 local youths will get to learn about open data, its importance and applications. The event will bring together youths from different sectors and educational backgrounds.

Data Expeditions are quests to map uncharted territory, discover hidden stories and solve unsolved mysteries in the land of data. Through these, participants learn about the value of open data as evidence for decision making and innovation. The Data Expedition involves participants teaming up to find data related to their local community, learning skills in accessing and understanding data from various sources, and developing ideas for open data-based solutions to local problems (such as datasets, maps, blogs, infographics, technical applications etc). 

OKN believes the outputs will show exciting information about development issues in Dang, and provide a starting point for participants to further engage with data to address development issues in their community. During the expedition participants will work on three thematic areas - health data, budget data and agriculture data.

Key Information
Date: March 2, 2019
Register: https://goo.gl/forms/WXDFyxZ1VHQIKlAe2
Venue: Hotel Doko (http://hoteldoko.com/), Ghorahi, Dang
Time: 09:00 AM - 05:00 PM
